'''Prismic's Avatar Search''' is a cross-platform [[:Category:Avatar worlds|avatar world]] published by Prismic247 in early 2023. In this world, users can search through an index of over a million [[Special:MyLanguage/Avatars|avatars]], as well as other gimmicks centred around avatars.

==Overview==
Prismic's Avatar Search places users into a box with grid textures for its floor and walls. It features a defaulted on [[Special:MyLanguage/Mirrors|mirror]], an avatar height indicator to the left and avatar search features to the right of spawn. Users can customize world visuals and players settings, as well as room options. 

==Features==
===Avatar search===
Towards the right of spawn, features the avatar search panel. Users have the ability to search for avatars by name, author and filter avatars by their [[Special:MyLanguage/Platforms|platform]], performance and whether they have [[Special:MyLanguage/Impostors|impostors]]. 

The avatar search works by collecting and indexing lists of known public avatars. Private avatars are not shown, and if avatar creators would like to get their avatars added or removed, simply follow the instructions shown in the world; contacting the author on Discord, or adding <code>[private]</code> to an avatar's description. 

After searching for an avatar, avatar pedestals will be displayed on the wall related to the result of the user's search. Users can also load any avatar via avatar ID. 

